1
00:00:05,276 --> 00:00:10,657
<i>This is the fifth case this year</i>
<i>of a girl being found strangled to death.</i>

2
00:00:11,157 --> 00:00:12,867
<i>According to investigators,</i>

3
00:00:12,951 --> 00:00:16,037
<i>they view these repeated cases as linked</i>

4
00:00:16,121 --> 00:00:18,039
<i>and are investigating accordingly.</i>

5
00:00:21,835 --> 00:00:23,753
What? You're going to be a dad?

6
00:00:23,837 --> 00:00:24,838
Yes.

7
00:00:24,921 --> 00:00:26,089
Congratulations!

8
00:00:26,172 --> 00:00:27,173
Congratulations!

9
00:00:27,257 --> 00:00:28,091
Thank you.

10
00:00:28,174 --> 00:00:30,718
I had no idea.
You should have told us!

11
00:00:30,802 --> 00:00:31,636
Sorry.

12
00:00:31,719 --> 00:00:34,264
Dr. Takamori,
I bet you'll be a great father.

13
00:00:34,973 --> 00:00:36,015
I wonder.

14
00:00:36,099 --> 00:00:37,142
We have to celebrate.

15
00:00:37,225 --> 00:00:38,476
No, you don't have to.

16
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:40,311
A pre-celebration drink.
A big one!

17
00:00:40,395 --> 00:00:42,814
-You just want to drink.
-No, I don't!

18
00:00:42,897 --> 00:00:44,691
Dr. Masumi is on vacation, right?

19
00:00:44,774 --> 00:00:45,817
Now is our chance.

20
00:00:47,193 --> 00:00:49,070
Hello, this is Medical Examiner Japan.

21
00:00:49,153 --> 00:00:51,823
How does the mindset
of becoming a father feel?

22
00:00:51,906 --> 00:00:53,157
I'm not sure.

23
00:00:53,241 --> 00:00:54,576
It hasn't really sunk in yet.

24
00:00:54,659 --> 00:00:55,994
When is the due date?

25
00:00:56,077 --> 00:00:57,620
For now, it's next weekend.

26
00:00:57,704 --> 00:00:58,663
Really?

27
00:00:58,746 --> 00:01:00,248
Hey, excuse me.

28
00:01:00,331 --> 00:01:02,876
We got a request
for an examination of a living person.

29
00:01:03,877 --> 00:01:07,755
A child suspected of being abused
was in an accident.

30
00:01:10,717 --> 00:01:12,844
<i>Clinical forensic medicine, right?</i>

31
00:01:12,927 --> 00:01:14,137
Yes.

32
00:01:14,220 --> 00:01:16,306
It's rare, isn't it?

33
00:01:16,389 --> 00:01:19,392
Until now, we've only done
examinations on bodies.

34
00:01:19,475 --> 00:01:21,352
With domestic violence, abuse,

35
00:01:21,436 --> 00:01:25,023
or other special cases, we sometimes
get asked to do an examination.

36
00:01:25,106 --> 00:01:26,733
What should we do?

37
00:01:26,816 --> 00:01:27,901
<i>Unfortunately,</i>

38
00:01:27,984 --> 00:01:29,819
I can't come back yet.

39
00:01:30,695 --> 00:01:33,615
Could you all handle it by yourself?

40
00:01:33,698 --> 00:01:36,701
What? Without you?

41
00:01:37,201 --> 00:01:40,622
Clinical forensic medicine
is Dr. Takamori's specialty.

42
00:01:41,205 --> 00:01:42,540
<i>I'll let him handle it.</i>

43
00:01:46,961 --> 00:01:48,171
I understand.

44
00:01:48,254 --> 00:01:50,673
All right, then. Thank you.

45
00:01:54,093 --> 00:01:55,261
That's unusual.

46
00:01:55,345 --> 00:01:57,263
Dr. Masumi never dumps a job
on someone else.

47
00:01:57,347 --> 00:01:58,806
<i>That's true.</i>

48
00:01:59,390 --> 00:02:00,934
<i>I wonder where he's going.</i>

49
00:02:06,231 --> 00:02:07,899
Sorry we're late.

50
00:02:07,982 --> 00:02:10,276
Huh? That doctor isn't here today?

51
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:12,695
He couldn't quite make it today.

52
00:02:12,779 --> 00:02:14,364
Well, that helps.

53
00:02:19,327 --> 00:02:20,536
Explain it to them.

54
00:02:20,620 --> 00:02:21,454
Yes, ma'am.

55
00:02:21,537 --> 00:02:24,249
The victim is ten-year-old Kanata Togawa.

56
00:02:24,332 --> 00:02:28,586
A neighbor found him collapsed here,
and he was rushed to the hospital.

57
00:02:28,670 --> 00:02:32,298
He still hasn't regained consciousness
and is receiving treatment.

58
00:02:32,799 --> 00:02:35,677
We don't know yet
if it was an accident or a crime.

59
00:02:38,346 --> 00:02:42,433
What kind of findings suggest abuse?

60
00:02:42,517 --> 00:02:45,728
Bruises all over his body.
On his back, his arms, everywhere.

61
00:02:45,812 --> 00:02:48,564
But there were no reports
to the child consultation center.

62
00:02:48,648 --> 00:02:51,567
Also, I don't think it's relevant,

63
00:02:51,651 --> 00:02:53,444
but just to let you know…

64
00:02:53,528 --> 00:02:54,362
You're okay.

65
00:02:54,445 --> 00:02:55,363
The monster…

66
00:02:56,322 --> 00:02:58,282
The monster is coming.

67
00:02:59,075 --> 00:03:01,911
The black monster…

68
00:03:01,995 --> 00:03:04,747
He said that and then lost consciousness.

69
00:03:04,831 --> 00:03:05,832
Monster?

70
00:03:07,083 --> 00:03:08,501
We found a knife!

71
00:03:14,173 --> 00:03:17,468
Maybe he was attacked with this
by the person who was abusing him,

72
00:03:17,552 --> 00:03:18,845
and then fell from here?

73
00:03:18,928 --> 00:03:21,431
First, we need to find out
if there really was abuse.

74
00:03:21,514 --> 00:03:22,348
Yes, ma'am.

75
00:03:23,725 --> 00:03:25,476
Just imagining it

76
00:03:26,436 --> 00:03:27,687
is painful.

77
00:03:39,991 --> 00:03:40,908
Come in.

78
00:03:41,826 --> 00:03:43,036
Excuse me.

79
00:03:43,119 --> 00:03:44,746
I'm Kiryu from MEJ.

80
00:03:44,829 --> 00:03:45,997
I'm Takamori.

81
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:50,418
We received a request for an examination
because there's a suspicion of abuse.

82
00:03:50,501 --> 00:03:53,838
He hit his head quite hard,
so please be careful.

83
00:03:53,921 --> 00:03:54,922
Yes, sir.

84
00:04:00,011 --> 00:04:01,137
Kanata…

85
00:04:03,097 --> 00:04:04,223
I'm sorry.

86
00:04:06,476 --> 00:04:07,477
Please.

87
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:08,394
Okay.

88
00:04:38,091 --> 00:04:39,300
Are you all right?

89
00:04:40,718 --> 00:04:42,261
It's nothing.

90
00:04:49,769 --> 00:04:52,480
Are you Kanata's mother?

91
00:04:58,403 --> 00:05:03,408
I was at my part-time job
when I got the call.

92
00:05:03,908 --> 00:05:05,660
You must have been shocked.

93
00:05:06,369 --> 00:05:07,203
Yes.

94
00:05:08,746 --> 00:05:11,791
I'm sorry, but it seems
there are marks on Kanata's body

95
00:05:12,542 --> 00:05:16,129
that were unrelated to the accident.

96
00:05:16,212 --> 00:05:18,464
Do you have any idea what they might be?

97
00:05:21,926 --> 00:05:22,969
Ms. Togawa?

98
00:05:24,053 --> 00:05:25,346
I don't know.

99
00:05:25,430 --> 00:05:26,681
I'm sorry.

100
00:05:27,348 --> 00:05:29,684
Was Kanata at home alone today?

101
00:05:30,268 --> 00:05:31,769
I think so.

102
00:05:31,853 --> 00:05:33,688
Sorry for asking,

103
00:05:33,771 --> 00:05:36,732
but you were divorced
five years ago, right?

104
00:05:37,775 --> 00:05:40,027
Are you living alone with Kanata now?

105
00:05:41,195 --> 00:05:42,572
For the most part, yes.

106
00:05:42,655 --> 00:05:43,531
For the most part?

107
00:05:44,198 --> 00:05:47,869
The person I'm dating
also comes over sometimes.

108
00:05:50,621 --> 00:05:52,874
Where is that person now?

109
00:05:53,457 --> 00:05:55,501
I can't get in touch with him right now.

110
00:05:55,585 --> 00:05:57,628
I think he'll be back soon, though.

111
00:05:58,212 --> 00:06:00,798
Could you tell me more about him?

112
00:06:02,842 --> 00:06:03,926
Yes.

113
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:08,139
Kanata fell down the stairs
for some reason.

114
00:06:08,222 --> 00:06:10,975
He hit his head
on the landing midway down the stairs,

115
00:06:11,058 --> 00:06:14,270
resulting in a cerebral contusion
and an acute subdural hematoma.

116
00:06:14,353 --> 00:06:15,605
There are also…

117
00:06:16,981 --> 00:06:19,984
several other bruises
likely caused by hitting the stairs.

118
00:06:21,110 --> 00:06:24,280
Those are the injuries from the fall.

119
00:06:25,281 --> 00:06:27,658
So the rest are from abuse.

120
00:06:28,576 --> 00:06:29,952
That's awful.

121
00:06:30,036 --> 00:06:32,079
Are these all abuse marks?

122
00:06:33,289 --> 00:06:34,707
I think so.

123
00:06:34,790 --> 00:06:36,751
The bruise marks can be covered up

124
00:06:36,834 --> 00:06:39,503
and are a characteristic of child abuse.

125
00:06:39,587 --> 00:06:42,882
There are many scar patches
and keloids on his back, too.

126
00:06:43,841 --> 00:06:45,218
Those are old wounds.

127
00:06:46,219 --> 00:06:48,638
These wounds on his arm
look fairly new, though.

128
00:06:49,305 --> 00:06:52,600
Coexisting old and new wounds
is also a characteristic of abuse.

129
00:06:53,476 --> 00:06:54,518
Doctor.

130
00:06:55,019 --> 00:06:56,896
This might be irrelevant,

131
00:06:56,979 --> 00:06:59,315
but when Kanata was being transported,

132
00:06:59,398 --> 00:07:01,442
<i>he said, "The black monster is coming."</i>

133
00:07:01,525 --> 00:07:03,027
<i>He seemed afraid.</i>

134
00:07:03,110 --> 00:07:05,112
The black monster?

135
00:07:05,196 --> 00:07:09,700
Maybe the person who abused him
looked that terrifying to him.

136
00:07:10,618 --> 00:07:11,744
But isn't it strange?

137
00:07:11,827 --> 00:07:14,247
If he was beaten by someone
who was abusing him,

138
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:16,832
he would likely say
"I was beaten by the monster."

139
00:07:16,916 --> 00:07:18,960
Instead he said, "The monster is coming."

140
00:07:19,544 --> 00:07:20,836
-True.
-No.

141
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:22,797
He hit his head and was confused.

142
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,757
Well, sure, but…

143
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:25,716
Anyway,

144
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:29,053
let's first investigate
what Kanata's daily life was like.

145
00:07:30,012 --> 00:07:30,972
-Okay.
-Okay.

146
00:07:46,654 --> 00:07:47,655
Come in.

147
00:07:51,242 --> 00:07:52,451
Excuse me.

148
00:07:59,792 --> 00:08:01,168
Long time no see.

149
00:08:01,669 --> 00:08:02,920
Professor Kujo.

150
00:08:05,590 --> 00:08:08,217
Has it been 15 years already?

151
00:08:09,677 --> 00:08:12,096
A lot of time has passed, hasn't it?

152
00:08:13,889 --> 00:08:15,182
I heard…

153
00:08:15,266 --> 00:08:17,268
I heard you're now working

154
00:08:17,768 --> 00:08:21,022
at a death investigation facility
established by the Ministry.

155
00:08:21,105 --> 00:08:21,981
Yes.

156
00:08:23,482 --> 00:08:26,402
Professor, how is your health?

157
00:08:29,155 --> 00:08:31,490
The cancer has spread all over.

158
00:08:31,574 --> 00:08:34,035
They say I have three months left.

159
00:08:37,413 --> 00:08:39,582
I've lived long enough.

160
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:41,959
I'll let myself…

161
00:08:43,628 --> 00:08:46,213
relax here for a little while longer.

162
00:08:49,216 --> 00:08:51,552
You mean Ms. Togawa from 401, right?

163
00:08:51,636 --> 00:08:53,721
I've heard screaming and things before.

164
00:08:53,804 --> 00:08:55,306
What kind of screaming?

165
00:08:55,389 --> 00:08:58,267
In the middle of the night,
suddenly, like "wahh!"

166
00:08:58,768 --> 00:09:01,354
I couldn't tell
what they were saying, though.

167
00:09:01,437 --> 00:09:03,564
It didn't use to be like that, though.

168
00:09:04,065 --> 00:09:06,817
The mom started dating
a scary-looking guy.

169
00:09:06,901 --> 00:09:08,069
That's when it started.

170
00:09:08,611 --> 00:09:12,156
I saw Kanata
crying a lot in the park once.

171
00:09:12,239 --> 00:09:14,575
How did Kanata look to you?

172
00:09:14,659 --> 00:09:15,660
He was terrified.

173
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:17,995
He was screaming.

174
00:09:18,079 --> 00:09:19,872
I felt so bad for him.

175
00:09:22,667 --> 00:09:24,377
I heard from the detective.

176
00:09:24,877 --> 00:09:26,087
I was shocked.

177
00:09:26,170 --> 00:09:28,964
To think that Kanata
would have an accident like that.

178
00:09:31,258 --> 00:09:34,470
Mr. Kamijo, since the divorce,
have you seen Kanata?

179
00:09:35,429 --> 00:09:37,848
I haven't seen him for years.

180
00:09:39,433 --> 00:09:40,851
We divorced

181
00:09:41,852 --> 00:09:44,355
because of my affair.

182
00:09:44,438 --> 00:09:46,190
I didn't feel like I could face him.

183
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,234
Sir…

184
00:09:48,943 --> 00:09:52,196
There's also a suspicion
that Kanata was being abused.

185
00:09:52,279 --> 00:09:54,073
Do you know anything about that?

186
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:56,951
I've heard rumors.

187
00:09:57,743 --> 00:09:58,744
I was worried.

188
00:09:59,328 --> 00:10:00,204
Rumors?

189
00:10:00,287 --> 00:10:03,165
Saya started dating a bad guy.

190
00:10:05,251 --> 00:10:07,169
If I had taken Kanata in,

191
00:10:07,878 --> 00:10:08,879
this would never…

192
00:10:13,467 --> 00:10:14,927
I should go see him.

193
00:10:16,053 --> 00:10:17,805
I could buy him some <i>kintsuba.</i>

194
00:10:20,099 --> 00:10:23,853
Even though he's a kid,
he loves Japanese sweets.

195
00:10:25,354 --> 00:10:27,314
I'm sure that would make him happy.

196
00:10:27,398 --> 00:10:30,568
But maybe his tastes have changed by now.

197
00:10:32,278 --> 00:10:33,696
I bet he has grown up.

198
00:10:36,782 --> 00:10:39,577
Ryoji Kida, 34 years old.
A construction worker.

199
00:10:39,660 --> 00:10:41,746
He's Saya Togawa's boyfriend.

200
00:10:41,829 --> 00:10:44,749
We haven't been able
to contact Kida since the incident,

201
00:10:44,832 --> 00:10:47,877
and it seems he didn't show up
for work today either.

202
00:10:48,627 --> 00:10:51,881
So the mother's boyfriend is the abuser.

203
00:10:51,964 --> 00:10:53,007
I think so.

204
00:10:53,758 --> 00:10:54,759
However…

205
00:10:55,384 --> 00:10:56,218
What?

206
00:10:56,302 --> 00:10:58,512
Regarding the knife that was found,

207
00:10:58,596 --> 00:11:02,057
it seems only Kanata's fingerprints
were detected on it.

208
00:11:02,141 --> 00:11:04,268
Kanata's? Not Kida's?

209
00:11:04,351 --> 00:11:05,227
Yes.

210
00:11:05,311 --> 00:11:06,687
And one more thing.

211
00:11:06,771 --> 00:11:07,605
What?

212
00:11:07,688 --> 00:11:10,065
Well, it might not be relevant, actually.

213
00:11:10,149 --> 00:11:11,358
Just say it.

214
00:11:11,442 --> 00:11:12,276
Yes, ma'am.

215
00:11:13,611 --> 00:11:15,821
Well, about Kida…

216
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:19,742
It seems he was abused himself
in the past.

217
00:11:19,825 --> 00:11:20,826
RYOJI KIDA

218
00:11:20,910 --> 00:11:22,119
He was?

219
00:11:22,203 --> 00:11:24,413
Ms. Kiryu said she heard it
from the police.

220
00:11:24,497 --> 00:11:28,542
Apparently, he was quite severely abused
by his stepfather when he was a child.

221
00:11:28,626 --> 00:11:32,004
Even though he was abused himself,
he abuses a child?

222
00:11:32,087 --> 00:11:34,423
Well, don't they say
people who were abused

223
00:11:34,507 --> 00:11:38,093
tend to become abusers themselves
when they grow up?

224
00:11:38,177 --> 00:11:41,096
Maybe because that's
the kind of parent they saw?

225
00:11:41,180 --> 00:11:43,641
A cycle of abuse, so to speak.

226
00:11:43,724 --> 00:11:46,185
Taking the pain you suffered
out on a child…

227
00:11:46,268 --> 00:11:48,103
Right…

228
00:12:05,287 --> 00:12:08,165
I'm glad you took the time to come.

229
00:12:10,834 --> 00:12:15,506
I was only able to get where I am
because of you, Professor.

230
00:12:17,424 --> 00:12:18,551
"Loved One."

231
00:12:21,345 --> 00:12:24,473
How to face a body.

232
00:12:26,392 --> 00:12:27,643
To doubt common sense,

233
00:12:28,143 --> 00:12:31,647
not to be bound by precedent,
and to have free thought.

234
00:12:33,524 --> 00:12:38,737
I was captivated by this field of study
because of your words.

235
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:41,991
You remember them well.

236
00:12:42,575 --> 00:12:43,617
But…

237
00:12:45,244 --> 00:12:47,079
during that case,

238
00:12:48,205 --> 00:12:50,207
you didn't do any of that, Professor.

239
00:13:00,718 --> 00:13:04,680
The Shiramine serial femicide case.

240
00:13:07,474 --> 00:13:09,143
You remember it, don't you?

241
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:16,233
I intend to face that case once more.

242
00:13:17,985 --> 00:13:19,403
Fifteen years ago…

243
00:13:19,486 --> 00:13:21,030
SHIRAMINE SERIAL FEMICIDE CASE
RESEARCH DATA

244
00:13:21,113 --> 00:13:24,366
<i>…I ran away from that case.</i>

245
00:13:24,867 --> 00:13:26,702
Even though I had doubts

246
00:13:27,494 --> 00:13:29,038
about your autopsy results.

247
00:13:31,206 --> 00:13:32,708
At that time,

248
00:13:32,791 --> 00:13:36,879
I didn't have the power or the knowledge
to overturn it.

249
00:13:37,796 --> 00:13:38,881
But now,

250
00:13:39,465 --> 00:13:42,635
I might be able
to unravel the contradictions.

251
00:13:45,012 --> 00:13:46,889
Please tell me, Professor.

252
00:13:48,182 --> 00:13:51,769
What really happened
behind the scenes of that case?

253
00:14:03,030 --> 00:14:04,948
Well, isn't this a rare visitor?

254
00:14:06,533 --> 00:14:07,534
Kyoko.

255
00:14:08,410 --> 00:14:10,412
Don't push my father too hard.

256
00:14:14,625 --> 00:14:17,294
I'm sorry for coming
at such a difficult time.

257
00:14:25,344 --> 00:14:26,470
I'll come again.

258
00:14:27,554 --> 00:14:28,389
Okay.

259
00:14:44,154 --> 00:14:45,531
You're back.

260
00:14:47,658 --> 00:14:49,284
How long will you be in Japan?

261
00:14:49,868 --> 00:14:51,453
For a while.

262
00:14:54,581 --> 00:14:56,375
You haven't changed at all.

263
00:14:56,875 --> 00:14:58,460
That's not true.

264
00:15:04,299 --> 00:15:06,719
You've heard about my father, right?

265
00:15:08,137 --> 00:15:09,430
He has little time left.

266
00:15:12,266 --> 00:15:13,434
I want him

267
00:15:14,476 --> 00:15:17,312
to be able to forget everything
and pass away in peace.

268
00:15:21,650 --> 00:15:24,194
The serial murders happening recently…

269
00:15:27,322 --> 00:15:29,700
They're similar
to the Shiramine murder case.

270
00:15:29,783 --> 00:15:31,452
There might be a connection.

271
00:15:35,914 --> 00:15:38,208
Even if there is a connection,

272
00:15:38,917 --> 00:15:41,003
it has nothing to do
with you or my father.

273
00:15:42,337 --> 00:15:43,714
Don't come back.

274
00:15:45,090 --> 00:15:46,550
You should forget it too.

275
00:16:04,234 --> 00:16:09,239
<i>This is the fifth case this year</i>
<i>of a girl being found strangled to death.</i>

276
00:16:10,824 --> 00:16:13,035
<i>They're similar</i>
<i>to the Shiramine murder case.</i>

277
00:16:13,118 --> 00:16:14,828
You should forget it too.

278
00:16:21,585 --> 00:16:23,754
Kanata has apparently
been terrified at school

279
00:16:23,837 --> 00:16:26,256
for about a year,
saying he didn't want to go home.

280
00:16:27,549 --> 00:16:30,886
That matches the time
Ms. Togawa started dating Kida.

281
00:16:31,470 --> 00:16:32,846
It does.

282
00:16:33,639 --> 00:16:34,515
Detective Dojima.

283
00:16:34,598 --> 00:16:35,599
What?

284
00:16:35,682 --> 00:16:37,309
Kida has turned himself in.

285
00:16:41,021 --> 00:16:42,815
Like I said,

286
00:16:42,898 --> 00:16:44,900
Kanata was being annoying.

287
00:16:44,983 --> 00:16:47,319
He never listened to me,

288
00:16:47,402 --> 00:16:50,072
so sometimes I slapped him,
telling him to be quiet.

289
00:16:51,073 --> 00:16:52,658
It was the same that day.

290
00:16:52,741 --> 00:16:55,160
He wouldn't stop crying,
and was bothering others.

291
00:16:55,744 --> 00:16:56,995
<i>So,</i>

292
00:16:57,079 --> 00:16:58,580
<i>I gave him a light push.</i>

293
00:17:03,627 --> 00:17:05,254
I'm sorry for running away.

294
00:17:05,337 --> 00:17:06,797
But I just panicked.

295
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:09,007
What about the knife we found
at the scene?

296
00:17:09,091 --> 00:17:10,217
No idea.

297
00:17:11,426 --> 00:17:13,512
It's not related to the incident?

298
00:17:14,596 --> 00:17:16,849
Calling it an incident or abuse…

299
00:17:16,932 --> 00:17:19,560
All I did was discipline him a little.

300
00:17:20,185 --> 00:17:21,770
Discipline, you say?

301
00:17:21,854 --> 00:17:22,896
That's right.

302
00:17:22,980 --> 00:17:26,400
That was just a little discipline.

303
00:17:26,483 --> 00:17:28,360
<i>This is just some discipline.</i>

304
00:17:28,443 --> 00:17:29,862
<i>I'm sorry!</i>

305
00:17:29,945 --> 00:17:30,946
<i>Don't cry!</i>

306
00:17:31,029 --> 00:17:32,364
<i>I'm sorry!</i>

307
00:17:33,490 --> 00:17:35,200
<i>I'm sorry!</i>

308
00:17:37,077 --> 00:17:38,203
Dr. Takamori?

309
00:17:39,705 --> 00:17:42,082
Are you okay? Dr. Takamori?

310
00:17:43,125 --> 00:17:44,543
Hey, are you okay?

311
00:17:44,626 --> 00:17:46,003
How is Kida?

312
00:17:46,086 --> 00:17:48,589
He's in the holding cell now
and is being quiet.

313
00:17:48,672 --> 00:17:50,883
He said he doesn't need
a lawyer or any visitors.

314
00:17:50,966 --> 00:17:52,050
That's great, right?

315
00:17:52,134 --> 00:17:53,510
The case was solved easily.

316
00:17:53,594 --> 00:17:55,470
I don't think it's solved.

317
00:17:55,971 --> 00:17:57,055
What?

318
00:18:07,316 --> 00:18:08,734
Are you okay?

319
00:18:17,117 --> 00:18:18,660
I'm sorry.

320
00:18:18,744 --> 00:18:19,953
No, not at all.

321
00:18:23,832 --> 00:18:27,502
Go home for the day and get some rest.

322
00:18:28,295 --> 00:18:30,589
We need you to get well soon.

323
00:18:31,298 --> 00:18:32,674
Since you'll be a dad.

324
00:18:41,308 --> 00:18:42,809
I don't have the confidence.

325
00:18:48,315 --> 00:18:49,858
I was abused, too.

326
00:18:51,401 --> 00:18:52,611
A long time ago.

327
00:18:56,782 --> 00:18:58,533
By my stepfather.

328
00:19:01,787 --> 00:19:04,331
When he got drunk, he would get violent.

329
00:19:07,042 --> 00:19:09,461
I still have the scars.

330
00:19:10,963 --> 00:19:12,839
They're on my back.

331
00:19:14,716 --> 00:19:16,802
They're very similar to Kanata's scars.

332
00:19:18,845 --> 00:19:23,100
I'm sorry for making you remember
something so unpleasant.

333
00:19:27,312 --> 00:19:28,814
I didn't remember it.

334
00:19:30,774 --> 00:19:32,734
It's always in my head.

335
00:19:34,111 --> 00:19:35,362
Kida…

336
00:19:38,323 --> 00:19:41,285
was also abused by his parents.

337
00:19:44,746 --> 00:19:46,248
And now,

338
00:19:46,873 --> 00:19:49,042
he's the one abusing a child.

339
00:19:53,547 --> 00:19:54,923
I'm scared…

340
00:19:58,719 --> 00:20:00,137
that one day…

341
00:20:03,598 --> 00:20:07,019
I might also end up raising
my hand against my own child.

342
00:20:07,102 --> 00:20:09,563
No, you would never.

343
00:20:18,655 --> 00:20:19,865
But maybe…

344
00:20:22,576 --> 00:20:24,953
because you experienced that,

345
00:20:26,830 --> 00:20:28,999
there is something you can do.

346
00:20:32,169 --> 00:20:34,129
I think you're the one who understands

347
00:20:35,589 --> 00:20:38,258
how much Kanata suffers

348
00:20:39,843 --> 00:20:42,012
better than anyone, Dr. Takamori.

349
00:21:00,364 --> 00:21:01,740
I'm sorry…

350
00:21:04,159 --> 00:21:05,535
Kanata.

351
00:21:26,098 --> 00:21:29,976
MY CHECKUP IS DONE
THEY SAID THE BABY IS VERY HEALTHY!

352
00:21:55,293 --> 00:21:56,711
<i>This is Masumi.</i>

353
00:21:57,921 --> 00:22:01,341
This is Takamori.
Sorry for calling while you're on leave.

354
00:22:01,425 --> 00:22:03,635
<i>No, it's fine.</i>

355
00:22:04,344 --> 00:22:05,720
Did something happen?

356
00:22:10,559 --> 00:22:14,563
I'm sorry for leaving
the investigation entirely to you.

357
00:22:15,063 --> 00:22:17,649
I've heard about the situation
from Ms. Kiryu.

358
00:22:19,443 --> 00:22:22,320
I don't know what to do.

359
00:22:25,365 --> 00:22:27,409
The suspect turned himself in,

360
00:22:28,618 --> 00:22:30,912
but I feel like nothing
has been solved yet.

361
00:22:34,332 --> 00:22:37,878
I was wondering what you would do
in a situation like this.

362
00:22:40,338 --> 00:22:41,840
<i>If it were me,</i>

363
00:22:42,465 --> 00:22:44,926
<i>I would re-examine</i>
<i>the remaining contradictions.</i>

364
00:22:45,427 --> 00:22:47,053
Like, the wounds on the arm.

365
00:22:47,137 --> 00:22:51,141
<i>Those wounds were arranged in parallel</i>
<i>with a certain regularity.</i>

366
00:22:52,184 --> 00:22:56,688
In cases of abuse, scars and bruises
would be scattered randomly,

367
00:22:56,771 --> 00:22:59,649
not perfectly parallel.

368
00:22:59,733 --> 00:23:01,026
It doesn't add up.

369
00:23:04,070 --> 00:23:08,450
<i>But, please keep in mind,</i>
<i>this is just how I would do it.</i>

370
00:23:09,784 --> 00:23:14,623
How one faces forensic medicine
is free and different for everyone.

371
00:23:15,832 --> 00:23:17,083
Dr. Takamori,

372
00:23:17,792 --> 00:23:20,795
how will you solve this mystery?

373
00:23:29,679 --> 00:23:32,140
Dr. Takamori is late, isn't he?

374
00:23:32,224 --> 00:23:33,934
There's no point in waiting.

375
00:23:34,017 --> 00:23:35,769
Let's start with what we can do.

376
00:23:35,852 --> 00:23:37,938
Sorry, I'm late.

377
00:23:38,021 --> 00:23:39,522
Dr. Takamori.

378
00:23:39,606 --> 00:23:43,777
I've decided
to try and find the truth one more time.

379
00:23:45,820 --> 00:23:49,741
I've reclassified Kanata's scars
based on their characteristics.

380
00:23:51,117 --> 00:23:52,994
Contusions on the head from the fall.

381
00:23:53,078 --> 00:23:55,914
Bruises and burn marks,
which suggest abuse.

382
00:23:55,997 --> 00:23:58,583
And systematic wounds on the left arm.

383
00:23:58,667 --> 00:23:59,960
Looking at them like this,

384
00:24:00,043 --> 00:24:03,171
they each seem to be wounds
inflicted in different ways.

385
00:24:03,255 --> 00:24:04,256
Right.

386
00:24:04,339 --> 00:24:05,632
That's easy to understand.

387
00:24:06,132 --> 00:24:09,302
So the arm wounds are the only ones
that are strange after all.

388
00:24:12,555 --> 00:24:17,102
I want everyone to analyze
these arm wounds in detail.

389
00:24:17,185 --> 00:24:18,019
Okay.

390
00:24:18,103 --> 00:24:18,937
Understood.

391
00:24:20,063 --> 00:24:21,064
What about you?

392
00:24:21,940 --> 00:24:23,149
I…

393
00:24:28,446 --> 00:24:29,864
A long time ago,

394
00:24:30,699 --> 00:24:32,784
I was abused by my stepfather.

395
00:24:38,415 --> 00:24:40,667
I looked back at my own experience.

396
00:24:42,002 --> 00:24:44,963
Abuse always happens inside the house.

397
00:24:45,547 --> 00:24:47,716
I'm going to look for clues there.

398
00:24:51,636 --> 00:24:54,723
I'm sorry for having you come
all the way out here with us.

399
00:24:54,806 --> 00:24:57,475
It can't be helped,
since the police need to be present.

400
00:24:57,559 --> 00:24:58,893
It's a big help.

401
00:25:00,645 --> 00:25:02,731
I want clues too.

402
00:25:09,529 --> 00:25:12,157
I'm sorry for taking up your time.

403
00:25:12,240 --> 00:25:16,369
Since it is such a serious case, we need
to investigate inside the home as well.

404
00:25:16,453 --> 00:25:20,165
I don't want to leave Kanata alone
for a long time…

405
00:25:20,665 --> 00:25:22,375
We won't stay long.

406
00:25:28,465 --> 00:25:29,549
Is something wrong?

407
00:25:30,884 --> 00:25:32,218
It's not roughed up.

408
00:25:34,429 --> 00:25:35,263
What?

409
00:25:37,849 --> 00:25:39,184
When there's abuse,

410
00:25:40,310 --> 00:25:43,021
there are marks
on the walls and everywhere.

411
00:25:43,104 --> 00:25:46,608
From going on a rampage
and throwing things and stuff.

412
00:25:48,651 --> 00:25:49,944
That's how it was at my place.

413
00:25:54,616 --> 00:25:55,575
Here you go.

414
00:25:55,658 --> 00:25:57,243
Please, don't trouble yourself.

415
00:25:58,661 --> 00:25:59,954
Thank you very much.

416
00:26:00,038 --> 00:26:01,456
Have some of this too.

417
00:26:02,874 --> 00:26:05,168
He likes them, so I bought some.

418
00:26:12,300 --> 00:26:13,843
Those are nice photos.

419
00:26:18,765 --> 00:26:20,850
That was Kida's influence too.

420
00:26:21,684 --> 00:26:25,397
He does martial arts,
so he said he watches his calories

421
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:28,316
and chooses Japanese
sweets over Western ones,

422
00:26:28,983 --> 00:26:31,027
so Kanata started eating them to copy him.

423
00:26:31,694 --> 00:26:33,905
Forgive me for asking, Saya,

424
00:26:33,988 --> 00:26:38,326
but did you not notice that Kida
was committing abuse?

425
00:26:40,787 --> 00:26:41,955
Or perhaps,

426
00:26:42,622 --> 00:26:45,166
did you not think he was committing abuse?

427
00:26:46,876 --> 00:26:48,962
I don't know.

428
00:26:50,880 --> 00:26:51,840
Well then,

429
00:26:51,923 --> 00:26:53,967
what about the "monster"?

430
00:26:55,009 --> 00:26:59,180
The "black monster" Kanata mentioned
when he was being transported.

431
00:26:59,764 --> 00:27:01,391
Do you have any ideas?

432
00:27:07,605 --> 00:27:09,315
I only vaguely remember…

433
00:27:11,276 --> 00:27:13,903
I might have read him
a picture book about that.

434
00:27:14,487 --> 00:27:15,738
A picture book?

435
00:27:16,781 --> 00:27:18,074
THE BLACK MONSTER

436
00:27:18,158 --> 00:27:22,912
<i>The Black Monster,</i>
a picture book published in the '80s.

437
00:27:24,330 --> 00:27:25,665
One night,

438
00:27:25,748 --> 00:27:29,919
a black monster appears before a child
who does nothing but play pranks.

439
00:27:30,003 --> 00:27:32,547
Eerie hands stretch out from the darkness

440
00:27:32,630 --> 00:27:34,841
and wrap around the child.

441
00:27:35,550 --> 00:27:38,094
He desperately resisted,
and drove it away.

442
00:27:38,178 --> 00:27:41,055
But after that,
every time he did something bad,

443
00:27:41,139 --> 00:27:44,142
the black hands
would wrap around the child again.

444
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:46,603
In the end,

445
00:27:46,686 --> 00:27:50,023
the black hands wrapped around
the child's arms and wouldn't let go,

446
00:27:50,106 --> 00:27:53,610
and he finally ended up
becoming a black monster himself.

447
00:27:53,693 --> 00:27:54,986
The end.

448
00:27:55,487 --> 00:27:57,697
Why is it such a hopeless story?

449
00:27:59,073 --> 00:28:01,784
A lesson not to do bad things?

450
00:28:02,619 --> 00:28:07,373
If the thing Kanata feared
was the monster from this picture book…

451
00:28:21,346 --> 00:28:22,430
Kanata?

452
00:28:24,140 --> 00:28:25,058
Kanata!

453
00:28:27,769 --> 00:28:28,978
Kanata…

454
00:28:34,692 --> 00:28:35,902
Kanata,

455
00:28:36,736 --> 00:28:39,447
can you talk to us for just a little bit?

456
00:28:41,366 --> 00:28:42,242
Yes.

457
00:28:42,325 --> 00:28:43,159
Thank you.

458
00:28:44,828 --> 00:28:47,956
Do you remember what happened
when you fell down the stairs?

459
00:28:56,005 --> 00:28:57,173
I don't know.

460
00:28:57,966 --> 00:29:00,260
I don't really remember.

461
00:29:01,302 --> 00:29:02,428
I see.

462
00:29:04,305 --> 00:29:07,725
It looks like you have quite
a few injuries besides your head.

463
00:29:09,477 --> 00:29:11,104
Where did you get hurt?

464
00:29:16,693 --> 00:29:20,530
Can I look at your wounds
for just a second?

465
00:29:21,281 --> 00:29:22,448
Yes.

466
00:29:26,619 --> 00:29:27,537
Sorry.

467
00:29:34,794 --> 00:29:35,712
Kanata!

468
00:29:35,795 --> 00:29:37,964
I'm scared, I'm scared!

469
00:29:38,047 --> 00:29:39,507
The monster is coming!

470
00:29:39,591 --> 00:29:41,593
The black monster!

471
00:29:43,219 --> 00:29:44,304
Kanata!

472
00:29:47,181 --> 00:29:49,017
I'm sorry, that's enough for today.

473
00:29:50,018 --> 00:29:51,269
Kanata.

474
00:29:51,352 --> 00:29:52,312
You'll be okay.

475
00:29:53,313 --> 00:29:55,189
Doctor, what's that?

476
00:29:55,273 --> 00:29:57,692
This is Kanata's head MRI.

477
00:29:57,775 --> 00:30:00,653
-Something is bugging me.
-Bugging you?

478
00:30:01,654 --> 00:30:02,822
This.

479
00:30:03,740 --> 00:30:04,741
What is it?

480
00:30:08,536 --> 00:30:12,373
<i>Those wounds were arranged in parallel</i>
<i>with a certain regularity.</i>

481
00:30:13,207 --> 00:30:14,417
<i>In the end,</i>

482
00:30:14,500 --> 00:30:17,253
<i>the black hands wrapped around</i>
<i>the child's arms and wouldn't let go,</i>

483
00:30:17,337 --> 00:30:19,881
<i>and he finally ended up</i>
<i>becoming a black monster himself.</i>

484
00:30:19,964 --> 00:30:21,424
<i>The black monster!</i>

485
00:30:23,843 --> 00:30:25,303
Dr. Takamori?

486
00:30:25,887 --> 00:30:26,930
Now…

487
00:30:27,722 --> 00:30:29,641
the pieces might be coming together.

488
00:30:33,186 --> 00:30:35,563
What else do you want?
I already told you everything.

489
00:30:35,647 --> 00:30:36,940
No, you haven't.

490
00:30:37,023 --> 00:30:39,067
I need you to tell me the truth.

491
00:30:39,692 --> 00:30:40,610
What?

492
00:30:40,693 --> 00:30:45,531
You weren't the one abusing Kanata.

493
00:30:53,081 --> 00:30:55,208
How is Kanata doing?

494
00:30:56,501 --> 00:30:59,170
Are you not going to see him, Mr. Kamijo?

495
00:31:00,505 --> 00:31:02,340
Well, even if I did…

496
00:31:03,257 --> 00:31:04,592
It was you, wasn't it?

497
00:31:05,635 --> 00:31:07,679
You were the one abusing Kanata.

498
00:31:09,722 --> 00:31:11,265
What kind of nonsense is that?

499
00:31:11,349 --> 00:31:13,685
Looking at Kanata's head MRI,

500
00:31:13,768 --> 00:31:16,854
there is slight atrophy
in the temporal and frontal lobes.

501
00:31:17,438 --> 00:31:18,314
Atrophy?

502
00:31:18,398 --> 00:31:22,485
This is a characteristic seen in children
who have been abused in the past.

503
00:31:22,568 --> 00:31:25,279
It is said that
the emotional scars received

504
00:31:25,363 --> 00:31:27,532
manifest in the brain.

505
00:31:29,283 --> 00:31:31,494
Kanata's scars are also unnatural.

506
00:31:31,577 --> 00:31:33,454
The wounds on his back and thighs

507
00:31:33,538 --> 00:31:36,332
<i>have a different color tone</i>
<i>compared to the others.</i>

508
00:31:36,416 --> 00:31:37,333
<i>Those wounds</i>

509
00:31:37,917 --> 00:31:41,754
might date back much further
than a year ago,

510
00:31:42,255 --> 00:31:45,633
to before you even started dating Saya.

511
00:31:46,634 --> 00:31:47,927
In other words,

512
00:31:48,428 --> 00:31:51,014
he was being abused

513
00:31:51,723 --> 00:31:55,184
long before she met you.

514
00:31:55,268 --> 00:31:56,519
Mr. Kamijo,

515
00:31:57,437 --> 00:31:59,772
these are considered
wounds from past abuse

516
00:32:00,690 --> 00:32:02,942
that occurred when he was living with you.

517
00:32:04,402 --> 00:32:06,362
Stop joking around.

518
00:32:06,446 --> 00:32:07,405
Why would I--

519
00:32:07,488 --> 00:32:09,240
You said it the other day, didn't you?

520
00:32:09,323 --> 00:32:11,409
That Kanata likes <i>kintsuba.</i>

521
00:32:11,492 --> 00:32:12,910
Of course I know what my son--

522
00:32:12,994 --> 00:32:17,373
Kanata only started liking <i>kintsuba</i>
after meeting Mr. Kida.

523
00:32:17,457 --> 00:32:19,500
That happened within the past year.

524
00:32:21,044 --> 00:32:24,338
You said you haven't seen him in years,
so how did you know?

525
00:32:26,257 --> 00:32:30,720
You've actually been seeing Kanata
over the past year, haven't you?

526
00:32:31,512 --> 00:32:32,764
<i>The question is,</i>

527
00:32:32,847 --> 00:32:36,768
why are you protecting Kamijo,
when you have nothing to do with him?

528
00:32:39,228 --> 00:32:40,688
I don't know.

529
00:32:41,355 --> 00:32:42,982
I'm not protecting anybody.

530
00:32:43,066 --> 00:32:48,362
The important clue for us
was the parallel wounds

531
00:32:48,446 --> 00:32:50,823
<i>carved into Kanata's left arm.</i>

532
00:32:50,907 --> 00:32:52,950
Normally, if someone
continued to abuse a person,

533
00:32:53,034 --> 00:32:55,453
the wounds would be more random.

534
00:32:56,704 --> 00:32:58,039
But those wounds

535
00:32:58,539 --> 00:33:01,834
were placed systematically,
in the same spot

536
00:33:01,918 --> 00:33:04,045
over and over again in the same way.

537
00:33:05,379 --> 00:33:08,091
They aren't scars
from abuse by another person.

538
00:33:09,509 --> 00:33:13,888
They're scars that Kanata
was inflicting on himself.

539
00:33:14,514 --> 00:33:16,682
<i>to stop the black monster from coming.</i>

540
00:33:16,766 --> 00:33:19,936
The black monster is coming… The monster…

541
00:33:22,146 --> 00:33:23,898
Three months ago,

542
00:33:23,981 --> 00:33:26,275
during a drinking session
with old friends,

543
00:33:26,359 --> 00:33:29,612
you apparently heard
that Saya had a new lover.

544
00:33:30,530 --> 00:33:33,866
You seemed to have become very jealous.

545
00:33:36,077 --> 00:33:37,912
-Coming!
<i>-So then…</i>

546
00:33:38,496 --> 00:33:40,414
<i>You went to Saya's home.</i>

547
00:33:43,126 --> 00:33:44,377
Please leave.

548
00:33:44,460 --> 00:33:46,629
What's the big deal? I'm your ex-husband.

549
00:34:00,810 --> 00:34:02,311
Are you her new boyfriend?

550
00:34:03,354 --> 00:34:04,605
Please leave.

551
00:34:09,277 --> 00:34:10,862
You've grown, Kanata.

552
00:34:13,281 --> 00:34:14,198
Hey.

553
00:34:14,907 --> 00:34:17,743
Daddy's talking to you.
You should answer.

554
00:34:18,327 --> 00:34:22,290
<i>Past memories of being beaten</i>
<i>flashed back to Kanata.</i>

555
00:34:23,166 --> 00:34:27,962
<i>To resist the trauma,</i>
<i>so that the black monster wouldn't come,</i>

556
00:34:28,045 --> 00:34:29,797
Kanata, it's okay.

557
00:34:29,881 --> 00:34:31,883
-The monster…
-Go away, now!

558
00:34:32,466 --> 00:34:34,135
I'm scared! Stop!

559
00:34:34,218 --> 00:34:35,303
Kanata!

560
00:34:35,386 --> 00:34:36,596
What is this?

561
00:34:36,679 --> 00:34:38,347
No, the monster!

562
00:34:38,431 --> 00:34:40,266
-Hey, Kanata!
-The monster…

563
00:34:42,852 --> 00:34:44,145
It's okay now.

564
00:34:44,228 --> 00:34:45,188
You're okay.

565
00:34:48,733 --> 00:34:49,609
All right!

566
00:34:50,359 --> 00:34:52,570
You're doing it. Go!

567
00:34:58,826 --> 00:35:00,453
I'm scared!

568
00:35:00,536 --> 00:35:02,288
-No!
-It's okay.

569
00:35:02,371 --> 00:35:04,457
-Should we do something?
-No! Stop!

570
00:35:04,540 --> 00:35:07,752
-You're okay!
<i>-Kanata's flashbacks kept coming back.</i>

571
00:35:08,753 --> 00:35:13,716
You wanted to help him somehow,
didn't you?

572
00:35:13,799 --> 00:35:15,259
If you're a man,

573
00:35:15,343 --> 00:35:18,429
you've got to become
strong enough to help your mom.

574
00:35:19,805 --> 00:35:21,307
-But…
-You can do it.

575
00:35:23,184 --> 00:35:24,352
Kanata,

576
00:35:25,311 --> 00:35:26,812
you're strong.

577
00:35:28,773 --> 00:35:31,609
I'm… strong?

578
00:35:31,692 --> 00:35:32,735
Yes.

579
00:35:37,782 --> 00:35:41,702
<i>Thanks to Mr. Kida,</i>
<i>Kanata gradually began to recover.</i>

580
00:35:42,787 --> 00:35:44,747
But then the incident happened…

581
00:35:46,624 --> 00:35:49,377
because you came to Kanata's house again.

582
00:35:51,087 --> 00:35:52,171
Probably,

583
00:35:52,255 --> 00:35:54,548
<i>what happened on that day was…</i>

584
00:35:55,299 --> 00:35:57,260
TOGAWA

585
00:36:02,098 --> 00:36:02,932
What?

586
00:36:03,641 --> 00:36:05,059
Saya's not here?

587
00:36:05,142 --> 00:36:06,269
Where's Saya?

588
00:36:06,852 --> 00:36:07,853
Where did she go?

589
00:36:18,531 --> 00:36:19,740
I am…

590
00:36:21,534 --> 00:36:22,618
strong.

591
00:36:23,286 --> 00:36:24,370
<i>But…</i>

592
00:36:24,996 --> 00:36:26,372
<i>Kida's teachings…</i>

593
00:36:27,456 --> 00:36:29,125
<i>backfired.</i>

594
00:36:52,606 --> 00:36:54,191
Don't talk nonsense.

595
00:36:54,692 --> 00:36:55,943
It wasn't me.

596
00:36:56,777 --> 00:36:58,487
Saya's boyfriend has confessed.

597
00:36:59,572 --> 00:37:00,489
Yes.

598
00:37:03,617 --> 00:37:05,453
After being threatened by you.

599
00:37:08,831 --> 00:37:10,541
From my perspective,

600
00:37:10,624 --> 00:37:14,378
I just went to the house
and was almost stabbed to death.

601
00:37:15,171 --> 00:37:17,923
This is a clear case of attempted murder.

602
00:37:19,467 --> 00:37:21,093
You've got to be kidding me.

603
00:37:21,177 --> 00:37:22,762
What about you abusing him?

604
00:37:22,845 --> 00:37:25,431
You can't prove something
from that long ago.

605
00:37:26,974 --> 00:37:28,267
On the other hand,

606
00:37:28,976 --> 00:37:31,228
Kanata has strange delusions
and self-harms,

607
00:37:31,312 --> 00:37:33,731
and tries to stab people to death.

608
00:37:36,692 --> 00:37:38,152
He'll go to a detention center.

609
00:37:42,990 --> 00:37:45,117
Just say that you did it.

610
00:37:46,535 --> 00:37:48,204
If you want to save Kanata,

611
00:37:51,499 --> 00:37:52,833
you know what to do.

612
00:37:58,047 --> 00:37:59,173
Mr. Kida…

613
00:38:01,926 --> 00:38:03,094
You had no choice--

614
00:38:03,177 --> 00:38:04,220
I did it.

615
00:38:06,722 --> 00:38:08,140
That's enough, isn't it?

616
00:38:12,186 --> 00:38:13,479
Actually,

617
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:16,065
before I came here…

618
00:38:18,025 --> 00:38:20,069
Saya told me everything.

619
00:38:25,366 --> 00:38:27,535
I HAVE TO SAY I DID IT, FOR KANATA'S SAKE

620
00:38:27,618 --> 00:38:29,203
<i>After the incident,</i>

621
00:38:29,829 --> 00:38:33,082
<i>she was told</i>
<i>to match what you were going to say,</i>

622
00:38:33,666 --> 00:38:36,168
<i>and she has been hesitant about it</i>
<i>the entire time.</i>

623
00:38:37,253 --> 00:38:39,672
No matter what the police ask you,

624
00:38:40,381 --> 00:38:42,007
just say you don't know.

625
00:38:43,300 --> 00:38:44,802
What about Ryoji?

626
00:38:45,970 --> 00:38:47,304
Where is he?

627
00:38:48,305 --> 00:38:49,640
He's okay.

628
00:38:50,891 --> 00:38:51,976
It'll be fine.

629
00:38:53,060 --> 00:38:54,145
<i>She wondered</i>

630
00:38:55,104 --> 00:38:57,273
<i>if this was really for the best.</i>

631
00:38:58,899 --> 00:39:00,776
There's no way this is a solution.

632
00:39:02,903 --> 00:39:05,865
After all, Kanata likes Ryoji, too.

633
00:39:11,579 --> 00:39:13,330
He really loves him.

634
00:39:17,001 --> 00:39:18,836
That's what Saya said.

635
00:39:24,925 --> 00:39:26,802
The one you were trying to protect

636
00:39:27,803 --> 00:39:29,555
and keep safe

637
00:39:31,307 --> 00:39:33,058
was Kanata, wasn't it?

638
00:39:48,949 --> 00:39:49,909
Yes?

639
00:39:51,827 --> 00:39:56,415
Do you understand how heartbreaking it is
to be beaten by your own parent?

640
00:39:58,709 --> 00:40:01,795
Scars from being beaten by
someone you want to be loved by most

641
00:40:03,464 --> 00:40:05,341
stay with you for a lifetime.

642
00:40:11,555 --> 00:40:12,890
How…

643
00:40:13,682 --> 00:40:16,852
can you do something
so cruel to your own child?

644
00:40:19,271 --> 00:40:23,692
Protecting your precious child
is what a father does, isn't it?

645
00:40:30,407 --> 00:40:31,408
I will never…

646
00:40:35,579 --> 00:40:39,875
become a parent like you.

647
00:41:00,854 --> 00:41:03,566
Mr. Kida has apparently
retracted his confession.

648
00:41:05,192 --> 00:41:06,402
Mr. Kamijo.

649
00:41:07,319 --> 00:41:09,405
Could you come talk with us
at the station?

650
00:41:22,334 --> 00:41:23,877
Feels nice outside, right?

651
00:41:23,961 --> 00:41:24,920
Yeah.

652
00:41:32,386 --> 00:41:33,637
Hey!

653
00:41:33,721 --> 00:41:34,680
It's Ryoji!

654
00:41:36,682 --> 00:41:37,808
Kanata.

655
00:41:43,564 --> 00:41:45,441
I'm not going anywhere anymore.

656
00:41:47,818 --> 00:41:49,528
From now on, we'll always be together.

657
00:41:55,784 --> 00:41:56,827
I…

658
00:41:58,579 --> 00:42:00,831
will make you and your mom happy.

659
00:42:04,043 --> 00:42:05,252
Got it?

660
00:42:06,337 --> 00:42:07,338
Yeah!

661
00:42:22,436 --> 00:42:23,979
Isn't this great?

662
00:42:27,191 --> 00:42:29,318
The cycle of abuse can be broken.

663
00:42:31,612 --> 00:42:32,863
I will break it.

664
00:42:33,364 --> 00:42:34,615
I will.

665
00:42:46,627 --> 00:42:47,795
Good morning.

666
00:42:58,389 --> 00:43:00,599
Oh, Dr. Masumi.

667
00:43:00,683 --> 00:43:02,017
Good morning.

668
00:43:02,101 --> 00:43:03,477
Sorry for waking you.

669
00:43:03,560 --> 00:43:04,770
It's fine.

670
00:43:04,853 --> 00:43:06,897
It's already this late?

671
00:43:09,525 --> 00:43:10,567
Doctor…

672
00:43:13,612 --> 00:43:14,947
Thank you very much.

673
00:43:18,784 --> 00:43:22,204
I am very glad I relied on you,
Dr. Takamori.

674
00:43:25,624 --> 00:43:26,792
Good morning.

675
00:43:26,875 --> 00:43:28,085
Oh! Dr. Masumi!

676
00:43:28,168 --> 00:43:29,378
Good morning.

677
00:43:29,461 --> 00:43:32,548
It was tough without you here.

678
00:43:32,631 --> 00:43:34,425
For Dr. Takamori, it was.

679
00:43:34,508 --> 00:43:35,634
Sure, but…

680
00:43:36,301 --> 00:43:38,387
We should get him
to treat you to something.

681
00:43:38,971 --> 00:43:39,930
No, that's all right.

682
00:43:49,565 --> 00:43:50,566
What?

683
00:43:50,649 --> 00:43:52,609
Oh, dear…

684
00:43:52,693 --> 00:43:53,694
Is something wrong?

685
00:43:53,777 --> 00:43:54,945
Well…

686
00:43:55,028 --> 00:43:57,114
-My wife is in labor.
-What?

687
00:43:57,197 --> 00:43:58,991
-She's about to give birth.
-What?

688
00:43:59,074 --> 00:44:00,409
-What should I do?
-Just go!

689
00:44:00,492 --> 00:44:02,202
Don't worry about things here.

690
00:44:02,286 --> 00:44:03,162
I'm going then!

691
00:44:03,245 --> 00:44:04,204
-Take care!
-Sorry.

692
00:44:04,288 --> 00:44:06,039
-Hey, hey, hey!
-Oh, my bag.

693
00:44:07,124 --> 00:44:08,584
-Be careful!
-Thank you.

694
00:44:08,667 --> 00:44:10,043
-See you!
-Bye!

695
00:44:10,127 --> 00:44:11,378
Bye!

696
00:44:23,682 --> 00:44:25,976
Subtitle translation by: Maslin F.

